{"title":"A. Countdown","contestId":"1573","problemIndex":"0","timeLimit":"1 second","memLimit":"256 megabytes","inputFormat":"standard input","outputFormat":"standard output","problemHtml":"<p>You are given a digital clock with $$$n$$$ digits. Each digit shows an integer from $$$0$$$ to $$$9$$$, so the whole clock shows an integer from $$$0$$$ to $$$10^n-1$$$. The clock will show leading zeroes if the number is smaller than $$$10^{n-1}$$$.</p><p>You want the clock to show $$$0$$$ with as few operations as possible. In an operation, you can do one of the following: </p><ul> <li> decrease the number on the clock by $$$1$$$, or </li><li> swap two digits (you can choose which digits to swap, and they don&apos;t have to be adjacent). </li></ul><p>Your task is to determine the minimum number of operations needed to make the clock show $$$0$$$.</p>","inSpecsHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Input</div><p>Each test contains multiple test cases. The first line contains the number of test cases $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \\le t \\le 10^3$$$).</p><p>The first line of each test case contains a single integer $$$n$$$ ($$$1 \\le n \\le 100$$$) &#x2014; number of digits on the clock.</p><p>The second line of each test case contains a string of $$$n$$$ digits $$$s_1, s_2, \\ldots, s_n$$$ ($$$0 \\le s_1, s_2, \\ldots, s_n \\le 9$$$) &#x2014; the number on the clock.</p><p>Note: If the number is smaller than $$$10^{n-1}$$$ the clock will show leading zeroes.</p>","outSpecsHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Output</div><p>For each test case, print one integer: the minimum number of operations needed to make the clock show $$$0$$$.</p>","noteHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Note</div><p>In the first example, it&apos;s optimal to just decrease the number $$$7$$$ times.</p><p>In the second example, we can first swap the first and last position and then decrease the number by $$$1$$$.</p><p>In the third example, the clock already shows $$$0$$$, so we don&apos;t have to perform any operations.</p>","sampleTestcases":[{"id":1631975761536,"input":"7\n3\n007\n4\n1000\n5\n00000\n3\n103\n4\n2020\n9\n123456789\n30\n001678294039710047203946100020","output":"7\n2\n0\n5\n6\n53\n115\n","result":{"id":1631975761536,"stdout":"7\r\n2\r\n0\r\n5\r\n6\r\n53\r\n115\r\n","stderr":"","exitcode":0,"signal":null,"time":54,"timeout":false}}],"submitUrl":"https://codeforces.com/contest/1573/submit","language":"c++","langId":"54"}